    "Figure 1 shows a step-by-step illustration.",
    "A colonoscopy involves performing an endoscopic examination of the large bowel and the rectum to diagnose a specific condition.",
    "We inserted a colonoscope, a long, flexible tube with a high-definition camera and illumination, through the rectum and slowly progressed it through the colon to conduct the test.",
    "The colonoscope's advancements permit the recording of live videos and still images of the intestinal lining.",
    "Gastroenterologists subsequently analyse these images to detect polyps, ulcers, or tumours."
